0{"DateTime":"2023-12-20T16:49:42.0049394Z","Version":0,"CopilotSessionId":{"Guid":"4095fa6a-a267-47b7-b57a-2cef9374c6fd","ClientId":{"Id":"Microsoft.VisualStudio.Conversations.Chat.HelpWindow"}},"Request":{"Prompt":"Allegedly, based on #file:ContractorsPlan.cshtml:1-3:1 , the Data is being fetched from the MembershipPlanFromStrip model, but when we look at that document #file:MembershipPlanViewmodel.cs , it is just a bunch of \u0022setters\u0022 and \u0022geters\u0022, but there is no API calls being made","Context":{"VisibleDocuments":[],"PreSelectedSkill":null,"CorrelationId":{"Guid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"}}},"Response":{"Content":"In MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture, the ViewModel is a class that contains the properties necessary to display data on the view. The ViewModel does not typically contain logic to fetch data, such as API calls. Instead, it\u0027s the responsibility of the Controller to fetch the data, populate the ViewModel, and then pass it to the View.\n\nIn your case, the \u0060MembershipPlanFromStrip\u0060 model in \u0060ContractorsPlan.cshtml\u0060 is likely populated in the Controller before it\u0027s passed to the View. The Controller would make the necessary API calls to Stripe, fetch the data, and then populate the \u0060MembershipPlanFromStrip\u0060 model with this data.\n\nHere\u0027s a simplified example of how this might look:\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060csharp\npublic class ContractorsPlanController : Controller\n{\n    public ActionResult Index()\n    {\n        var service = new Stripe.PriceService();\n        var price = service.Get(\u0022price_id\u0022); // replace \u0022price_id\u0022 with the actual id of the price you want to fetch\n\n        var model = new MembershipPlanFromStrip\n        {\n            Price = price.UnitAmount\n        };\n\n        return View(model);\n    }\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nIn this example, the \u0060Index\u0060 action of the \u0060ContractorsPlanController\u0060 is fetching the price from Stripe, populating the \u0060MembershipPlanFromStrip\u0060 model with this price, and then passing the model to the View.\n\nTo find out where the data for \u0060MembershipPlanFromStrip\u0060 is coming from, you would need to look at the Controller that is responsible for the \u0060ContractorsPlan.cshtml\u0060 view.","Type":0,"Status":1,"FollowUpPrompts":["Can you explain more about MVC architecture?","How can I optimize the data fetching process in the controller?"]},"SelectedFunctionName":"Explain","LoggedSkillInvocations":null,"ThreadName":null}
